20that%20the%20US%20has%20left%20behind.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20appears%20to%20be%20launching%20new%20programs%20across%20several%20developing%20countries%20where%20USAID%20has%20left%20%E2%80%94%20as%20analysts%20forecast%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusaid-shutdown-china-trump-musk-investment-belt-and-road-initiative-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20February.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20Cambodia%20%E2%80%94%20one%20of%20the%20countries%20most%20hit%20by%20USAID's%20pullout%20%E2%80%94%20China%20has%20announced%20new%20funding%20programs%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20causes%2C%20including%20child%20healthcare%2C%20nutrition%2C%20sanitation%2C%20and%20landmine%20clearing.%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EIn%20Nepal%2C%20Chinese%20Communist%20Party%20officials%20have%20told%20the%20country's%20leaders%20that%20Beijing%20is%20willing%20to%20provide%20funding%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheannapurnaexpress.com%2Fstory%2F52229%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnnapurna%20Express.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETai%20Wei%20Lim%2C%20a%20professor%20at%20Japan's%20Soka%20University%2C%20told%20BI%20that%20it's%20not%20surprising%20that%20China%20stepped%20in%20so%20fast%20to%20fill%20the%20US's%20shoes%20for%20specific%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump%20flagged%20his%20intention%20to%20shut%20USAID%20well%20in%20advance%2C%20so%20China%20%E2%80%94%20a%20strategic%20competitor%20%E2%80%94%20had%20time%20to%20strategize%2C%20said%20Lim%2C%20who%20specializes%20in%20the%20political%20economy%20of%20Northeast%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20China%20is%20an%20economic%20superpower%20with%20a%20unique%20highly-centralized%20state%2C%20it%20can%20mobilize%20its%20enormous%20resources%20relatively%20easily%20to%20spaces%20where%20it%20sees%20opportunities%20in%20furthering%20its%20goals%20and%20objectives%20aligned%20with%20national%20interests%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Lim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChina%20has%20long%20focused%20on%20infrastructure%20and%20construction%20projects%20in%20other%20countries.%20Beijing%20could%20also%20look%20to%20other%20sectors%20that%20China%20already%20leads%2C%20like%20agriculture%20and%20public%20health.%20That%20could%20boost%20the%20country's%20bottom%20line%20and%20its%20publicity%20efforts%2C%20said%20Jeremy%20Chan%2C%20a%20senior%20analyst%20on%20the%20China%20and%20Northeast%20Asia%20team%20at%20the%20risk%20consultancy%20Eurasia%20Group.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeijing%20is%20also%20likely%20to%20target%20locations%20in%20its%20sphere%20of%20influence%2C%20including%20Southeast%20Asia%2C%20South%20Asia%2C%20and%20Central%20Asia.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChan%20said%20even%20though%20China%20is%20opportunistically%20filling%20in%20the%20gaps%20in%20some%20USAID%20programs%2C%20there's%20no%20broader%20trend%20yet%20of%20Beijing%20stepping%20into%20the%20US's%20big%20shoes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChinese%20media%20has%20not%20reported%20higher%20foreign%20aid%20plans%2C%20%26quot%3Bor%20the%20triumphalist%20propaganda%20that%20we%20would%20expect%20to%20accompany%20a%20broader%20strategic%20shift%20in%20Beijing's%20approach%20to%20development%20assistance%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Chan.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20said%20it's%20unlikely%20China%20will%20be%20able%20to%20fill%20most%20of%20the%20void%20left%20by%20USAID's%20withdrawal%2C%20so%20other%20countries%20from%20northeast%20Asia%20and%20Europe%20would%20step%20up%20their%20funding%20where%20it%20suits%20their%20interests.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSAID%20spent%20%2432.5%20billion%20in%20fiscal%20year%202024.%20Exact%20figures%20for%20China's%20foreign%20aid%20spending%20aren't%20fully%20public%2C%20but%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%20nofollow%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1080%2F24761028.2024.2316532%23abstract%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eestimates%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20Japanese%20academics%20put%20the%20country's%2020