2C%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20hiring%20has%20been%20sluggish%20and%20more%20like%20the%202010s%20than%20the%20booming%20market%20of%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EKathleen%20Nolan%2C%20who's%20been%20a%20technical%20recruiter%20for%20about%20seven%20years%2C%20knows%20how%20tough%20the%20job%20market%20is.%20She%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.linkedin.com%2Fposts%2Fkathleenmanagesit_jobsearch-hiring-recruiting-activity-7299805335907618816-7UeA%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ELinkedIn%20post%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20she%20reassured%20a%20job%20seeker%20she%20rejected%20that%20it%20was%20the%20job%20market%2C%20not%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20thinks%20companies%20%26quot%3Bare%20only%20opening%20roles%20when%20and%20if%20they%20are%20truly%20needed%2C%20and%20they%20are%20doing%20their%20best%20to%20not%20pad%20head%20count%20more%20than%20necessary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you've%20never%20had%20a%20problem%20getting%20a%20job%20before%20and%20suddenly%20you%20do%2C%20you%20can't%20look%20at%20it%20and%20think%2C%20'I'm%20the%20problem%2C'%26quot%3B%20Nolan%20said.%20%26quot%3BYou've%20got%20to%20look%20at%20what's%20going%20on%20around%20you.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20industries%20have%20more%20opportunities%20than%20others.%20Zhao%20said%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgen-z-hot-jobs-tech-layoffs-healthcare-government-careers-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ehealthcare%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20not%20as%20subject%20to%20the%20business%20cycle%20as%20other%20sectors.%20Cory%20Stahle%2C%20an%20economist%20at%20the%20Indeed%20Hiring%20Lab%2C%20said%20there's%20a%20lot%20of%20hiring%20happening%20in%20this%20sector%2C%20while%20tech%20and%20other%20knowledge%20worker%20gigs%20aren't%20seeing%20as%20much%20hiring.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20don't%20choose%20what%20time%20you're%20in%20the%20job%20market%2C%20but%20you%20can%20choose%20which%20part%20of%20the%20job%20market%20you%20focus%20on%2C%26quot%3B%20Zhao%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22ee8ce9a8-c88c-4c6e-a96e-e094ef4a53a4%5C%22%3EToo%20many%20applicants%20for%20a%20role%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20jobs%20that%20are%20available%2C%20employers%20may%20not%20have%20enough%20hands%20to%20go%20through%20or%20respond%20to%20each%20applicant.%20Nolan%20said%20talent%20acquisition%20and%20similar%20roles%20took%20a%20hit%20during%20the%20pandemic%2C%20and%20companies%20haven't%20expanded%20these%20teams%20to%20their%20previous%20levels.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BYou%20have%20fewer%20people%20to%20go%20through%20more%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsee-resume-that-landed-jobs-at-google-and-meta-2024-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20to%20fill%20fewer%20jobs%2C%20but%20it's%20still%20quite%20a%20bit%20of%20work%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBonnie%20Dilber%2C%20a%20recruiter%20for%20about%20a%20decade%2C%20said%20her%20current%20employer%2C%20a%20software%20company%2C%20had%20to%20pause%20an%20application%20for%20a%20job%20with%20a%20few%20openings%20after%20getting%20700%20applicants%20within%20a%20few%20days%20of%20being%20posted.%20Dilber%20said%20many%20of%20the%20people%20were%20well-qualified%20for%20the%20role.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20was%20just%20seeing%20that%20a%20lot%20of%20people%20who%20really%20have%20the%20skills%20and%20could%20probably%20do%20the%20job%20pretty%20well%20are%20not%20even%20going%20to%20be%20able%20to%20get%20interviews%20because%20there%20are%20just%20so%20many%20people%20who%20are%20also%20on%20the%20market%20competing%20for%20a%20small%20number%20of%20jobs%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%221dff5cd4-5811-4579-aa82-acbd9915fd4c%5C%22%3EThere's%20no%20true%20formula%20for%20getting%20a%20job%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThere%20could%20be%20things%20you%20can%20do%20to%20try%20to%20move%20along%20the%20job%20process.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDilber%20doesn't%20recommend%20applying%20to%20every%20job%20opening%20you%20see%20and%20instead%20focusing%20on%20postings%20you%20are%20%26quot%3Bwell%20qualified%26quot%3B%20for.%20%26quot%3BMass%20applying%20is%20actually%20hurting%20people%20because%20they're%20putting%20in%20lower%20quality%20applications%20that%20aren't%20going%20to%20stand%20up%20in%20a%20competitive%20applicant%20tool%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20doesn't%20think%20there's%20a%20clear%20formula%20for%20standing%20out%20in%20the%20job%20search%20or%20getting%20that%20first%20interview.%20However%2C%20she%20recommends%20strategic%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-network-for-new-job-microsoft-vp-hr-explains-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Enetworking%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20reaching%20out%20to%20existing%20connections%20and%20to%20people%20you%20admire%20in%20your%20field%20of%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSomething%20that%20can%20sometimes%20be%20underrated%20is%20asking%20for%20what%20you%20want%2C%20putting%20it%20out%20there%2C%20whether%20it's%20on%20LinkedIn%2C%20whether%20it's%20writing%20an%20email%20to%20folks%20you%20might%20know%20in%20your%20industry%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENolan%20said%20your%20LinkedIn%20profile%20should%20be%20a%20version%20of%20your%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcant-get-job-what-to-never-always-include-resume-hiring-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Er%C3%A9sum%C3%A9%3C%2Fa%3E%20because%20recruiters%20tend%20to%20check%20it%20in%20addition%20to%20r%C3%A9sum%C3%A9s%20submitted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBeyond%20doing%20the%20typical%20grunt%20work%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffind-job-searching-hunt-tips-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efinding%20a%20job%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Nolan%20said%20to%20be%20patient%20and%20to%20take%20care%20of%20yourself.%20She%20said%20applying%20for%20w